column5: I have been down there a few times and fishing has been poor, lots of people still go there though.
I take my son there to kill time pretty regularly. Tonnes of Gobies and Catfish. Nothing more than that though.

I was there most of sept. but got nothing. Haven't been since. Then again the salmon ran late this year. I heard there is a creek west of the rouge that is much more productive. A few weeks ago some friends were there hanging out, not fishing, and said they were jumping consistantly.
